lenders.name: Elizabeth:Dizzy Lizzie's Farm
lenders.loan_because: Dizzy Lizzie's Farm is a growing family farm that currently offers  vegetables, berries, maple syrup, cut flowers, and plants to the local community. This year the farm has applied for Organic certification for approved fields and we have begun the transitioning process for the rest. We have found with all of our rapid growth we have badly outgrown our current infrastructure and need a greenhouse to present better and more product to market. Once we have received certification we will be bringing in a new flock of chickens and will need a bigger coop.

lenders.name: Deutsche Bank
lenders.loan_because: For more than 20 years, Deutsche Bank has been a leader and trusted partner in the field of social finance. We are proud to support Kiva Zip as an important step towards triggering new levels of growth and job creation in New York.

lenders.name: The Diller-von Furstenberg Family Foundation
lenders.loan_because: We lend to borrowers in the United States, to empower entrepreneurs in our own backyard.

lenders.name: Milwaukee Economic Development Corporation (MEDC)
lenders.loan_because: The Milwaukee Economic Development Corporation (MEDC) serves Milwaukee businesses by providing low-interest loans. Our approach is unique in that we share the risk with all participants in a project, lend in partnership with a bank, and lend funds at a higher risk level in order to increase the feasibility of a project. Our goal is to give businesses the financial resources they need to grow, while facilitating business investment that will benefit Milwaukee through new employment opportunities, job retention, and neighborhood stabilization. Our support for Kiva Zip to provide matching loans at 0% interest to underserved businesses in the area aligns directly with this mission.

lenders.name: Rotary Club of Louisville
lenders.loan_because:
The Rotary Club of Louisville is looking for refugees and immigrants living in the Louisville Metro area who want to start or grow a business.  We match approved candidates one-for-one as they raise capital to start businesses that will support families and provide jobs for those looking for new opportunity. 
 
We lend not only capital but also our expertise to borrowers.  Interested borrowers can contact our club at rotary@rotary45.org for connections to organizations we partner with to prepare borrowers for success.

lenders.name: MetLife Foundation
lenders.loan_because: MetLife Foundation is committed to ensuring that individuals have access to the financial services they need to pursue more from life.  For us financial inclusion is about working with our partners to advance the delivery of high quality financial products and services to those who need it most. We are proud to support Kiva borrowers to help them expand their businesses and build for the future.

lenders.name: The Zisman Family Foundation
lenders.loan_because: The Zisman Family Foundation supports self-reliance through innovation and entrepreneurship.  We hope that our matching loans will help Kiva entrepreneurs make an impact in their Philadelphia communities.

lenders.name: Friends of Kiva Philadelphia
lenders.loan_because: The Friends of Kiva Philadelphia is a group of Greater Philadelphia residents who collaborated to offer matching loan dollars to Philadelphia entrepreneurs because we believe that small businesses are the backbone of our economy.

lenders.name: Investors' Circle Philadelphia
lenders.loan_because: Investors’ Circle Philadelphia provides capital and strategic counsel to early-stage venture growth companies in the Philadelphia region that are focused on solving meaningful social or environmental challenges.
